 \left|\frac1t(I(t)-I(t_0))+\frac1tI(t_0)-\frac{nT}t\cdot\frac1{T}I(T)\right|\leqslant\frac1tJ, 
T=\pi
I(\pi)=\int\limits_0^\pi\sin(x)\,\mathrm dx=2
\frac2\pi
\int_{k\pi+c}^{(k+1)\pi+c}|\sin x|\,dx=\int_0^\pi\sin x\,dx=2
1+k\pi \le n< 1+(k+1)\pi
k=\lfloor\frac{n-1}\pi\rfloor
2k\le \int_1^n|\sin x|\, dx\le 2(k+1)
\int_0^\pi\!dx\,\sin x = \int_\pi^{2\pi}\!dx\,|\sin x|=2.
n_- = \lfloor n/\pi \rfloor
\int_1^n\!dx\,|\sin x| = \underbrace{\int_1^\pi\!dx\,\sin x}_{1+\cos 1} +  \underbrace{\int_\pi^{n_-\pi}\!dx\,|\sin x|}_{2(n_- - 1)} +  \underbrace{\int_{n_- \pi}^n\!dx |\sin(x)|}_{1-\cos (n -n_- \pi)} .
